</tr>
<tr>
    <td class="text-nowrap">3.3.4 Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)</td>
    <td>AA</td>
    <td>
        The intent of this Success Criterion is to help users with disabilities avoid serious consequences as the result of a mistake when performing an action that cannot be reversed. 
        For example, purchasing non-refundable airline tickets or submitting an order to purchase stock in a brokerage account are financial transactions with serious consequences. 
        Also when deleting data about the user, error prevention should be used (it is not the intent to require a confirmation for each save command or the simple creation or editing of documents, records or other data).
        <br>
        <strong>It helps: Visually impaired, motor impaired, cognitive impaired</strong><br>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/error-prevention-legal-financial-data.html" target="_blank">
            WCAG: Understanding 3.3.4: Error Prevention (Legal, Financial, Data)
        </a>
    </td>
    <td>
        Provide a statet time for when the action can be reversed. <br>
        provide the ability for the user to review and change the inputs. <br>
        Provide a checkbox for the user to confirm the input. <br>
        Ask for user confirmation before performing any irreversible actions.
    </td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td class="text-nowrap">3.3.5 Help</td>
    <td>AAA</td>
    <td>
        The intent of this Success Criterion is to help users avoid making mistakes. 
        Some users with disabilities may be more likely to make mistakes than users without disabilities. 
        Using context-sensitive help, users find out how to perform an operation without losing track of what they are doing.
        <br>
        <strong>It helps: Cognitive impaired</strong><br>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/help.html" target="_blank">
            WCAG: Understanding 3.3.5: Help
        </a>
    </td>
    <td>
        Provide text instructions or help link. This could apply to both understanding
        content but also how to fill out forms (different input formats for example).
    </td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td class="text-nowrap">3.3.6 Error Prevention (All)</td>
    <td>AAA</td>
    <td>
        This criterion builds on Success Criterion 3.3.4 in that it applies to all forms that require users to submit information.
        <br>
        <strong>It helps: Visually impaired, motor impaired, cognitive impaired</strong><br>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/error-prevention-all.html" target="_blank">
            WCAG: Understanding 3.3.6: Error Prevention (All)
        </a>
    </td>
    <td>
        Following the sufficient techniques for Success Criterion 3.3.4 for all forms that require the user to submit information.
    </td>
</tr>
